Verifying constants


The sample might be 1 m², so for 100 m², it's PFT × 100 kg, but PFT is per m².
Then, dry matter for 100 m² is (PSM/PFM) × PFT × 100 kg, and for 1 ha, it's (PSM/PFM) × PFT × 10 t/ha.
I'm thinking the constants 0.1 and 0.04 account for area ratios, given the sampling method.
Let's set it equal; if Y = (PSM/PFM) × PFT in kg/m², total biomass per ha is Y × 10 t/ha, but the formula has × 0.1, which doesn't match.


